Solid, reliable and very accurate pistol.

title: For Sale:  Big Honkin' Bunch of Old Military Stuffs And Things. (Price Drop!)
postcontent:
Great big lot of old military stuff.

I'm going to try first to sell all of this stuff as one big lot. I know that by just looking at it all laying there at once, naked and metallic-y, that it may seem an awful much to wrap your head around. But give it a try. You can do it. I have great confidence in you and your abilities. You will also be doing us both a great service, so there is the humanitarian angle to think about. When was the last time you serviced the human race? Here is your big chance. By buying all of these little lovelies at once you will be saving me the trouble of making a bunch of separate postings. All one go, see? Easy-peasy! You will also be saving yourself a metric Scheiße-ton of money. And that, for you, is like money in the bank, my friend.

So. Here you will see a list of every thing in the photo, and its corresponding price if sold separately. At the conclusion we will refigure a super duper, all in, one time only, discount price, at which we will both rejoice and make merry. Got it? Alrighty.

WWII era canvas bandoleer for .303 Brit ammo. Empty.  $10
WWII era canvas bandoleer with five original SMLE stripper clips loaded with WWII era Mark VII Cordite Ball.  $35
8mm Lebel Hotchkiss machine gun tray/loading strip loaded with 24 rounds of 8mm Lebel ammo. $30
7.7mm Japanese semi-rim Hotchkiss type machine gun tray/loading strip loaded with 30 rounds of 7.7mm Japanese ammo. $30
8mm Lebel four, five shot en-bloc clips for the 8mm Lebel Mannlicher-Berthier carbine Mle 16 loaded with 8mm Lebel ammo.
   These will also work in the 3 shot carbine but will protrude from the bottom of the magazine.  $10 each = $40
M1 Garand en-bloc clip loaded with 8 rounds of ww2 dated 30-06 ammo.  $10
Mauser 98 5 round stripper clip loaded with 5 ww2 7.92x57mm rounds. These are head stamped K43 WIIZ which means they are British made AP rounds
    for the Breda machine gun. The Brits had these in their tanks but didn't have time to have them made in 303.  $10 Learnin' = free.
Argentine mauser 5 shot stripper clip loaded with 7.65mm Argentine. $5
7.35mm Italian 5 shot en-bloc clip loaded with 5 rounds of 7.35mm Carcano. $10
'03 Springfield 5 shot stripper clip loaded with five rounds of WW2 dated 30-06 ammo. $10
6.5 Arisaka 5 round stripper clip loaded with 5 rounds of 6.5mm Japanese WW2 ammo. $10
Mauser 1896 broom-handle pistol 10 shot stripper clip loaded with 9mm Parabellum. This example is DWM stamped and can be used for all calibers
    the broom-handle was chambered for. 9mmpara, 9mmMauser, and 30 Mauser. Obviously wont work c/ the Chinese 45s.  $10
8mm Kropatchek 1902 dated string tied paper package of 10,  8mm Kropatchek black powder, wooden bulleted, blanks. Plus 2 loose rounds. $15 
Linked WW2 dated 30-06. 14 rounds $10
Linked 7.62 NATO star crimp nosed blanks for the M-60? Links are a bit rusty/ratty.  $5
30-40 US Krag. 6 rounds of US Govt issue ammo for the 30-40 Krag Jorgenson rifle. Frankfort Arsenal 06 and 07 head stamp dates.
   Very good condition for these hard to find examples. Look almost brand new and over 100 years old. $15
50 caliber nick-knacks. 4 WW2 dated empties, 3 unprimed/unfired. 1 steel 50 cal armorers dummy round. 1 star crimped 50 cal Blank cartridge. 4 Fifty cal. projectiles. 2 ball, 1 tracer, 1 AP/API. (not sure on the last one.  $20.

There she be. That's one, big , spicy, meatball of military collectability to get down your gullet all at once, but you can do it. I know you can. I arrived at those prices by taking the low average of stuff I found online, and lots of other sources. Those arent unfair prices for real, genuine, of era stuffs in good condition and getting harder to find by the day. In fact, they are more than fair, they are outstanding! Just like me! Just like you! However, I'm willing to deal for convenience, simplicity, volume. The American Way! Just like 'Ol Ben Franklin(may his nose forever glow) All that adds up to $275 on the nose, and that's before shipping. (if you need shipping) If you hitch up your highwaters and take the whole shebang at once, I'll knock off 150 bucks. That's right, $125 measly, piddlin', rickyticky greenbacks for all that stuff. All that history! One stop shopping and whopping discounts, you can't beat 'em. If you need shipping, we're gonna have to work something out, but it can be done. I'll find the cheapest way if you give me your town and zip. I'm gonna let this run for a short time as only the whole package deal, then I'll re list everything separately at original price. Get that email/phone box aworkin! 

As always, Lee at 47987176fourfour.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Price Drop!! HOLD OUT ON BUYING PYTHONS AND COLTS!!
postcontent: Hey just giving shooters a heads up on Colts, especially Pythons. Just wait it out a bit longer if your looking to get one of these fine guns because the market is about to drop big time later this year. Unfortunately a lot of investors got into them for investments only which drove up the prices. This caused shooter like myself not to be able afford them because they went from $800-$1500 guns to now $2,000-$4,000 guns depending on which version you had. These puppies are made to be shot and not tossed back and forth between investors. Pythons are still very common online and offline, but thanks to investors who bought them at a $1000 to sell for $1500 and so on till now, investors are peaking. Investors are now stuck trying to sell a blued python for $2000+ and they aren't moving. Keep the waiting because if you go to the shows like I do and go online a lot you see they aren't moving like they use to. Hell some people are trying to get a MKIII Troopers which is a $500-600 gun all day for over $1000. These guns weren't built smooth and are a poor mans Python. My Smith 19 and Ruger with outlast troopers all day long and are much smoother to shoot. With this sluggish economy and Obamacare sticking it to people, no one is going to drop $2000 on a python. So keep holding out and watch the prices drop! This isn't anything different then when investors destroyed the Muscle Car market and the Comic book market. In the 90's certain comics sky rocketed and were valued in the hundreds and thousands of dollars, today you cant give them away, Those same comics can be bought online at Ebay for $5. SO HOLD OUT BECAUSE WHEN THE INVESTORS LEAVE THE PRICES WILL DROP!! I hope a lot of you investors take a huge hit!
